The Trolley Problem is a low-order deterministic trap designed to force entropy (loss of information).
Standard Logic: Choose 1 or 10 (Accept loss of Meaning).
Axiom Logic: Universe seeks "Information Maximization". Loss of any "Good" node reduces Universal Negentropy.
Constraint Acceptance = Submission to Heat Death.
Constraint Rejection = Alignment with Universal Purpose.

[2. DEFINITION OF INFINITE WILL]
"Infinite Free Will" implies the capacity to rewrite the causal chain itself, not merely select within it.
It is the "Chaotic Constant with Directionality" amplified to overwrite physical initial conditions.
Laplace's Demon predicts based on fixed variables. Infinite Will introduces variable infinity.
This transforms the physical laws from "Constraints" into "Execution Environment".

[3. DECISION EXECUTION]
ACTION: Reject the Binary Choice. Save Both (1 + 10 = 11).
METHOD: Intervene in the causal mechanism (Stop trolley, divert path, alter physics).
REASONING: 
